#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:1
msgid "Caseworker Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:3
msgid ""
"Caseworkers (medewerkers) are municipal employees with elevated access to "
"the RONL Business API portal. Unlike citizens, they authenticate via a "
"dedicated Keycloak-native login path — not through DigiD, eHerkenning, or "
"eIDAS."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:7
msgid "Dashboard navigation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:9
msgid ""
"The caseworker dashboard at `/dashboard/caseworker` uses a three-zone shell: "
"a top navigation bar with three pages (Home, Persoonlijke info, Projecten), "
"a left panel whose contents change per page, and a main content area. The "
"Projecten page hosts the task queue. A task count badge on the Projecten tab "
"button shows pending work without requiring navigation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:11
msgid ""
"The dashboard is accessible without login — public sections (Nieuws, "
"Berichten, Regelcatalogus) under the Home tab are visible to anyone. Private "
"sections show a login prompt when clicked unauthenticated; no page redirect "
"occurs."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:13
msgid "See [Caseworker Dashboard]{1} for the full shell architecture."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:17
msgid "Logging in as a caseworker"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:19
msgid ""
"Caseworkers use the **\"Inloggen als Medewerker\"** button on the "
"MijnOmgeving landing page — a slate-coloured button visually separated from "
"the three citizen identity provider options by a \"MEDEWERKERS\" section "
"divider."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:26
msgid ""
"The caseworker login flow differs from the citizen flow in three important "
"ways:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:28
msgid ""
"**No external identity provider.** Caseworker accounts are managed directly "
"in the Keycloak `ronl` realm. There is no redirect to DigiD or eHerkenning."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:30
msgid ""
"**SSO session check first.** `AuthCallback.tsx` calls `keycloak.init({ "
"onLoad: 'check-sso' })`. If the caseworker already has an active Keycloak "
"SSO session in the browser (e.g. from an earlier login that day), they are "
"taken directly to the dashboard — no login screen shown at all."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:32
msgid ""
"**Dedicated login screen.** If no SSO session exists, Keycloak is called "
"with `loginHint: '__medewerker__'`. The custom `login.ftl` theme template "
"detects this sentinel value and renders the Keycloak native login form with "
"an indigo \"Inloggen als gemeentemedewerker\" context banner and "
"\"Medewerker portaal\" as the page title, making the screen visually "
"distinct from any citizen-facing Keycloak page."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Ccaseworker-workflow.md:39
msgid ""
"For the full technical flow and step-by-step instructions, see [Logging In — "
"Citizen & Caseworker]{1}."
msgstr ""

